movie-1.title: Ludo
movie-1.description:
From a resurfaced sex tape to a rogue suitcase of money, four wildly
different stories overlap at the whims of fate, chance and one
eccentric criminal.
movie-1.extranote:
Anurag Basu directs this ensemble cast including Abhishek A.
Bachchan, Aditya Roy Kapur, Pankaj Tripathi and Rajkummar Rao.

movie-2.title: Puss in Boots
movie-2.description:
The fabled feline heads to the Land of Giants with friends Humpty
Dumpty and Kitty Softpaws on a quest to nab its greatest treasure:
the Golden Goose.
movie-2.extranote:
The fabled feline heads to the Land of Giants with friends Humpty
Dumpty and Kitty Softpaws on a quest to nab its greatest treasure:
the Golden Goose.

movie-3.title: Spider-Man: No Way Home
movie-3.description:
When his loved ones are put at risk, Peter Parker asks Doctor
Strange to restore his secret — and accidentally sets off
a disaster of epic proportions.
movie-3.extranote:
When his loved ones are put at risk,
Peter Parker asks Doctor Strange
to restore his secret

movie-4.title: 6 Underground
movie-4.description:
After faking his death, a tech billionaire recruits a team of
nternational operatives for a bold and bloody mission to take down a
brutal dictator.
movie-4.extranote:
After faking his death, a tech billionaire recruits a team of
nternational operatives for a bold and bloody mission to take down a
brutal dictator.

movie-5.title: Red Notice
movie-5.description:
An FBI profiler pursuing the world's most wanted art thief becomes
his reluctant partner in crime to catch an elusive crook who's always
one step ahead.
movie-5.extranote:
Dwayne Johnson, Ryan Reynolds and Gal Gadot chase each other
around the globe in this fun and funny action adventure.

movie-6.title: The Sea Beast
movie-6.description:
When a young girl stows away on the ship of a legendary sea
monster hunter, they launch an epic journey into uncharted waters -
and make history to boot.
movie-6.extranote:
A thrilling animated adventure for the whole family from the award-
winning filmmaker behind 'Moana' and 'Big Hero 6.'

movie-7.title: The Croods A New Age
movie-7.description:
While searching for a new home, the Croods discover a walled-in
paradise inhabited by the inventive Betterman family. Then it all goes
bananas.
movie-7.extranote:
Peter Dinklage, Leslie Mann and Kelly Marie Tran join the original
“Croods” voice cast for this sequel to the 2013 film.

movie-8.title: An Action Hero
movie-8.description:
A murder accusation turns a movie star's own life into an eccentric
action thriller as he flees the country, with a vengeful politician hot on
his heels.
movie-8.extranote:
A murder accusation turns a movie star's own life into an eccentric
action thriller as he flees the country, with a vengeful politician hot on
his heels.

movie-9.title: Uncharted
movie-9.description:
Street-smart treasure hunter Nathan Drake and his renegade mentor
Sully set out on a dangerous adventure across the globe to find
Magellan's lost gold.
movie-9.extranote:
Tom Holland, Mark Wahlberg and Antonio Banderas star in this
action adventure directed by Ruben Fleischer.

movie-10.title: The Croods
movie-10.description:
When an earthquake obliterates their cave, an unworldly prehistoric
family is forced to journey through unfamiliar terrain in search of a
new home.
movie-10.extranote:
A No. 1 hit at the box office, this animated adventure features the
voices of Nicolas Cage and Emma Stone.

movie-11.title: Bhool Bhulaiyaa 2
movie-11.description:
When strangers Reet and Ruhan cross paths, their journey leads to
an abandoned mansion and a dreaded spirit who has been trapped
for 18 years.
movie-11.extranote:
This horror-comedy sequel to the 2007 blockbuster film stars Kartik
Aaryan, Kiara Advani and Tabu.

movie-12.title: Thunivu
movie-12.description:
A major bank heist takes an unnerving turn when a mysterious
interloper known only as Dark Devil begins to hijack the operation.
movie-12.extranote:
A major bank heist takes an unnerving turn when a mysterious
interloper known only as Dark Devil begins to hijack the operation.

movie-13.title: Double XL
movie-13.description:
Relentlessly shamed for their weight, two women head to London to
prove that the size of their dreams is the only one that matters.
movie-13.extranote:
Relentlessly shamed for their weight, two women head to London to
prove that the size of their dreams is the only one that matters.

movie-14.title: Slumberland
movie-14.description:
Joined by a larger-than-life outlaw, a daring young orphan journeys
through a land of dreams to find a precious pearl that will grant her
greatest wish.
movie-14.extranote:
Jason Momoa stars with Marlow Barkley in this epic fantasy
adventure from the director of “The Hunger Games: Catching Fire.”

movie-15.title: Malang
movie-15.description:
Years after a police encounter separates him from his lover, an angry
young man goes on a killing spree, with an equally vengeful cop on
his heels.
movie-15.extranote:
Years after a police encounter separates him from his lover, an angry young man
goes on a killing spree, with an equally vengeful cop on his heels.

movie-16.title: Guillermo del Toro’s Pinocchio
movie-16.description:
Oscar-winning filmmaker Guillermo del Toro reinvents the classic
story of a wooden puppet brought to life in this stunning stop-
motion musical tale.
movie-16.extranote:
With the voices of Ewan McGregor, David Bradley, Gregory Mann,
Tilda Swinton, Finn Wolfhard, Christoph Waltz and more.

movie-17.title: The Gray Man
movie-17.description:
When a shadowy CIA agent uncovers damning agency secrets, he’s
hunted across the globe by a sociopathic rogue operative who’s put
a bounty on his head.
movie-17.extranote:
Ryan Gosling and Chris Evans star with Ana de Armas and Regé-
Jean Page in this global action thriller from the Russo brothers.

movie-18.title: Wonder Woman 1984
movie-18.description:
While working at the Smithsonian, secret superhero Diana Prince
discovers the miracle — and menace — of a mysterious artifact’s
staggering powers.
movie-18.extranote:
While working at the Smithsonian, secret superhero Diana Prince discovers the
miracle — and menace — of a mysterious artifact’s staggering powers.

movie-19.title: Re/Member
movie-19.description: Six high schoolers stuck in a murderous time loop must find the
movie-19.extranote:
Six high schoolers stuck in a murderous time loop must find the scattered
emains of an unknown victim to break the curse and finally see another day.

movie-20.title: Mowgli: Legend of the Jungle
movie-20.description:
An orphaned boy raised by animals in the jungle seizes his destiny
while confronting a dangerous enemy -- and his own human origins.
movie-20.extranote:
An orphaned boy raised by animals in the jungle seizes his destiny
while confronting a dangerous enemy -- and his own human origins.

movie-21.title: Troll
movie-21.description:
When an explosion in the Norwegian mountains awakens an ancient
troll, officials appoint a fearless paleontologist to stop it from
wreaking deadly havoc.
movie-21.cast: Ine Marie Wilmann,Kim Falck,Mads Sjøgård Pettersen
movie-21.extranote:
This fantasy-action film stars Ine Marie Wilmann (“War Sailor”) and
was directed by Roar Uthaug (“Tomb Raider”).

movie-22.title: Triple Frontier
movie-22.description:
Loyalties are tested when five former special forces operatives
reunite to steal a drug lord's fortune, unleashing a chain of
unintended consequences.
movie-22.extranote:
Starring Ben Affleck, Oscar Isaac and Charlie Hunnam. Directed by
Oscar nominee J.C. Chandor (“A Most Violent Year”).

movie-23.title: Raw (Beast)
movie-23.description:
A jaded former intelligence agent is pulled back into action when an
attack at a mall creates a tense hostage situation.
movie-23.extranote:
Vijay (“Master”) leads the cast featuring Pooja Hegde and Yogi Babu
in this action-thriller from director Nelson (“Doctor”).

movie-24.title: Saakini Daakini
movie-24.description:
Awkward situations abound when two women become cadets at a
male-dominated police academy, but the crime they uncover may be
their biggest test of all.
movie-24.extranote:
Awkward situations abound when two women become cadets at a male-dominated
police academy, but the crime they uncover may be their biggest test of all.

movie-25.title: Let There Be Carnage
movie-25.description:
While Eddie Brock and Venom try to navigate their thorny
relationship, a new threat rises from serial killer Cletus Kasady and a
new alien symbiote.
movie-25.extranote:
Andy Serkis directs this sequel starring Tom Hardy, Woody
Harrelson, Michelle Williams and Naomie Harris.

movie-26.title: Journey 2: The Mysterious Island
movie-26.description:
When a distress signal pinpoints his grandfather's location on an
uncharted island, teen Sean Anderson teams with an unlikely ally: his
stepfather.
movie-26.extranote:
Dwayne “The Rock” Johnson and Josh Hutcherson (“The Hunger
Games”) team up for a globetrotting adventure.

movie-27.title: Gunjan Saxena: The Kargil Girl
movie-27.description:
Flight Lieutenant Gunjan Saxena makes history in her journey from
aspiring aviator to India’s first female combat pilot in the Kargil War.
movie-27.extranote:
With Janhvi Kapoor (“Ghost Stories”) in the titular role, this inspiring
drama also stars Pankaj Tripathi (“Sacred Games”).

movie-28.title: The Angry Birds Movie
movie-28.description:
Sentenced to anger management class, grumpy Red becomes a
hero who trains his fellow birds to unleash their inner fury when pigs
invade their island.
movie-28.extranote:
Sentenced to anger management class, grumpy Red becomes a hero who
trains his fellow birds to unleash their inner fury when pigs invade their island.

movie-29.title: Now You See Me 2
movie-29.description:
With a new member in the fold, the Four Horsemen use their power
of illusion in a heist involving a shady tycoon and revolutionary tech
device.
movie-29.extranote:
With a new member in the fold, the Four Horsemen use their power of illusion
in a heist involving a shady tycoon and revolutionary tech device.

movie-30.title: Wrath of Man
movie-30.description:
An enigmatic employee of an armored truck company catches his
co-workers off guard when he unleashes his violent skills during an
attempted heist.
movie-30.extranote:
Jason Statham joins director Guy Ritchie for this action-thriller co-
starring Holt McCallany and Josh Hartnett.

movie-31.title: Qarib Qarib Singlle
movie-31.description:
After reluctantly joining a dating app, a 35-year-old widow
accompanies an easygoing poet on a trip to visit three of his exes.
movie-31.extranote:
After reluctantly joining a dating app, a 35-year-old widow
accompanies an easygoing poet on a trip to visit three of his exes.

movie-32.title: Badhaai Do
movie-32.description:
A gay cop and a lesbian teacher enter a sham marriage to pacify their
families but find that relationships — both real and fake — aren’t all
that easy.
movie-32.extranote:
Rajkummar Rao and Bhumi Pednekar lead this heartfelt family
dramedy from director Harshavardhan Kulkarni.

movie-33.title: Radhe Shyam (Hindi)
movie-33.description:
Convinced he isn't destined for love, a renowned palmist must
question everything he believes when he falls for a doctor with an
uncertain future.
movie-33.extranote:
Prabhas and Pooja Hegde lead the cast in this romantic period
drama from director Radha Krishna Kumar.

movie-34.title: Sooryavanshi
movie-34.description:
A fearless, faithful (and only slightly forgetful) Mumbai cop pulls out
all the stops — and stunts — to thwart a major conspiracy to attack
his city.
movie-34.extranote:
Akshay Kumar joins director Rohit Shetty's cop universe. Co-stars
Katrina Kaif, with cameos by Ajay Devgn and Ranveer Singh.

movie-35.title: Gangs of Wasseypur: Part 1
movie-35.description:
From a legacy built on thievery and crime, two families repeatedly
clash over lucrative territory in this tragic multigenerational saga.
movie-35.extranote:
Writer and director Anurag Kashyap’s (“Sacred Games”) explosive
crime saga premiered at Cannes and won three National Awards.

movie-36.title: Gangs of Wasseypur: Part 2
movie-36.description:
As two rival clans continue their bloody feud in a crime-ridden
mining town, the black sheep of one family steps up as leader, with
only one goal: kill.
movie-36.extranote:
This gangster epic was nominated for 10 Filmfare Awards, winning
for Best Film, Actress, Dialogue and Action.

movie-37.title: Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse
movie-37.description:
After being bitten by a radioactive spider, Brooklyn teen Miles
Morales gets a crash course in web-slinging from his alternate-
dimension counterparts.
movie-37.extranote:
With its ingenious visuals and inspiring story, “Spider-Verse” won
Best Animated Feature at the Oscars and Golden Globes.

movie-38.title: Baazaar
movie-38.description:
A wide-eyed graduate learns the ugly side of ambition when he joins
in the dubious business practices of his idol, a ruthless Mumbai stock
tycoon.
movie-38.extranote:
Saif Ali Khan (“Sacred Games”) and Radhika Apte (“Sacred Games,”
“Ghoul”) costar in this tale of money, power and greed.
